Developing flow-control strategies for fully turbulent 3D wakes around cylinders constitutes a significant challenge for DRL. As the wake becomes three-dimensional, the MARL setup must effectively utilize spanwise characteristic structures to devise efficient control methods, which can have profound implications for drag reduction. Note that DRL can discover new strategies by maximizing rewards \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
