				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\pi$$\end{document}π. In Fig. 3, we show how drag and lift coefficients evolves during exploitation for both models, DRL-10-s1 and DRL-10-s2, alongside the control law from KC05 and the uncontrolled case. The effectiveness of the KC05 strategy is evident, but, as will be discussed later, it requires significantly higher actuation cost. Focusing on DRL-based strategies first, we observe a successful reduction of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
