				\begin{document}$$20\%$$\end{document}20% rate of episodes starting from the uncontrolled case causes the agent to “forget” the transition process, trading it for improved stabilization of the reduction. Despite the improvement in low-frequency oscillations, the average reduction slightly worsens to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
