Figure 5a and b illustrate the benefits offered by a system like MARL. In comparison to what is observed at lower Reynolds numbers (Suárez et al. 2023), where it was clear that the control tries to synchronize all jets to act at the same frequency adapting to minimal instabilities, here we have a much richer control. As shown by the power-spectral density in Fig. 5c, Q evolution undergoing DRL-based control exhibits more features besides the main frequency \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
